2
00:02:13,287 --> 00:02:15,985
But you're off to Yamagata, right?

3
00:02:16,092 --> 00:02:17,081
Yes.

4
00:02:17,194 --> 00:02:19,425
Broke up with your boyfriend?

5
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:22,360
I just prefer the countryside.

6
00:02:22,479 --> 00:02:23,074
- See ya!

7
00:02:23,094 --> 00:02:23,689
- Bye!

8
00:02:24,105 --> 00:02:25,164
Let's go play!

9
00:02:25,274 --> 00:02:26,833
Bye now!

10
00:02:26,943 --> 00:02:28,674
Later!

11
00:02:29,715 --> 00:02:31,149
Did you get good grades?

12
00:02:31,328 --> 00:02:32,822
No.

13
00:02:32,842 --> 00:02:34,336
But I don't care.

14
00:02:34,457 --> 00:02:35,287
How come?

15
00:02:35,391 --> 00:02:38,557
As soon as I get home, we're traveling to Grandma's.

16
00:02:38,664 --> 00:02:40,963
So I won't get yelled at for ages.

17
00:02:41,079 --> 00:02:42,642
Lucky you!

18
00:02:42,662 --> 00:02:44,225
Are you going away too?

19
00:02:44,350 --> 00:02:45,782
Yeah, to Nagano.

20
00:02:45,802 --> 00:02:47,234
How about you, Taeko?

21
00:02:47,345 --> 00:02:48,244
I'm not sure.

22
00:02:48,548 --> 00:02:50,984
My Dad bought a summer place.

23
00:02:51,186 --> 00:02:52,745
Wow... that's great!

24
00:02:54,691 --> 00:02:57,628
Such a bad grade in math again.

25
00:02:58,331 --> 00:03:01,234
But I got a "B" in science.

26
00:03:01,703 --> 00:03:04,265
Are we going away for the holidays?

27
00:03:04,374 --> 00:03:05,808
Not really.

28
00:03:06,111 --> 00:03:08,547
Take me someplace.

29
00:03:09,159 --> 00:03:11,371
I'll take you to a movie.

30
00:03:11,391 --> 00:03:13,603
Find out what's playing.

31
00:03:13,734 --> 00:03:15,228
Not that.

32
00:03:15,248 --> 00:03:16,742
I mean to the country...

33
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:17,762
The country?

34
00:03:17,865 --> 00:03:20,232
Like Grandma's country house.

35
00:03:20,335 --> 00:03:21,826
Grandma lives with us.

36
00:03:21,947 --> 00:03:23,111
- Grandpa's then...

37
00:03:23,131 --> 00:03:24,295
- He's dead.

38
00:03:24,408 --> 00:03:28,507
We don't have relatives in the country, so don't ask.

39
00:03:32,656 --> 00:03:36,561
My family had lived in Tokyo for generations.

40
00:03:36,663 --> 00:03:39,725
I envied friends who had family in the countryside.

41
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:44,261
It's too late to book.

42
00:03:44,281 --> 00:03:45,792
All hotels will be full.

43
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:48,112
But I really want to go...

44
00:03:48,851 --> 00:03:50,547
What about "Onoya"?

45
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,760
We're regulars.

46
00:03:52,780 --> 00:03:54,810
They'd have a room for us.

47
00:03:54,928 --> 00:03:56,089
Where's that?

48
00:03:56,207 --> 00:03:57,917
Good idea.

49
00:03:57,937 --> 00:03:59,647
Taeko's never been there.

50
00:03:59,769 --> 00:04:00,930
That's right.

51
00:04:01,038 --> 00:04:03,804
Is it in the mountains... by the sea?

52
00:04:04,176 --> 00:04:05,805
It's in Atami.

53
00:04:07,014 --> 00:04:08,039
Atami?

54
00:04:08,150 --> 00:04:10,780
You get to ride the bullet train.

55
00:04:10,888 --> 00:04:12,881
Sure, you ll love it.

56
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:17,656
Atami...

57
00:04:17,766 --> 00:04:20,532
Lots of different hot springs...

58
00:04:20,771 --> 00:04:23,867
There's a huge Roman Bath.

59
00:04:23,977 --> 00:04:29,784
And others, like the Swan Bath and the Violet Bath.

60
00:04:29,887 --> 00:04:31,685
The beautiful Violet Bath!

61
00:04:32,826 --> 00:04:34,021
The Violet Bath...

62
00:04:34,171 --> 00:04:35,284
Oh yes.

63
00:04:35,304 --> 00:04:36,417
It's fantastic.

64
00:04:36,531 --> 00:04:38,364
You love hot springs, right?

65
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:42,838
Since father's working, you four go.

66
00:04:43,243 --> 00:04:44,336
What?!

67
00:04:47,917 --> 00:04:49,249
Us?

68
00:04:49,353 --> 00:04:50,787
Go too?!

69
00:04:57,534 --> 00:05:01,371
I'm amazed you show up every morning.

70
00:05:01,474 --> 00:05:04,172
Everyone else has left town.

71
00:05:06,049 --> 00:05:08,781
Aren't you going anywhere?

72
00:05:09,097 --> 00:05:09,777
- Yes, I am.

73
00:05:09,797 --> 00:05:10,477
- Where?

74
00:05:10,590 --> 00:05:11,648
Atami.

75
00:05:11,935 --> 00:05:13,480
Atami?

76
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,045
What's in Atami?

77
00:05:15,165 --> 00:05:16,963
Hot springs.

78
00:05:20,874 --> 00:05:22,399
It's good timing.

79
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:26,506
We're going away next week.

80
00:05:26,718 --> 00:05:30,178
No-one will be around for ages.

81
00:05:32,971 --> 00:05:33,884
Hello.

82
00:05:33,904 --> 00:05:34,817
Okajima residence.

83
00:05:34,942 --> 00:05:36,322
Nanako?

84
00:05:36,342 --> 00:05:37,722
It's Taeko.

85
00:05:37,847 --> 00:05:40,075
I leave today.

86
00:05:40,095 --> 00:05:42,323
Any message for your husband's family?

87
00:05:42,888 --> 00:05:45,100
Not really.

88
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:47,332
Just buy them something.

89
00:05:47,453 --> 00:05:50,288
Say it's from us and I'll pay you back.

90
00:05:50,402 --> 00:05:52,101
Don't worry about it.

91
00:05:52,121 --> 00:05:53,820
How's Mom?

92
00:05:53,930 --> 00:05:55,455
She's out today.

93
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:59,937
She was mad you turned down that guy's proposal.

94
00:06:00,175 --> 00:06:03,908
"At 27, that's the best offer she's going to get!"

95
00:06:04,014 --> 00:06:06,610
It's all she talks about.

96
00:06:06,729 --> 00:06:08,644
She's got a point.

97
00:06:08,664 --> 00:06:10,579
You're not young anymore...

98
00:06:10,692 --> 00:06:11,887
Oh, yeah?

99
00:06:11,995 --> 00:06:13,486
Definitely.

100
00:06:13,597 --> 00:06:15,999
You've got to settle down eventually.

101
00:06:16,102 --> 00:06:20,599
By the way, did you really work in the fields last year?

102
00:06:20,719 --> 00:06:22,532
Yes, harvesting rice.

103
00:06:22,552 --> 00:06:24,365
This year, I'm picking safflower.

104
00:06:24,483 --> 00:06:25,508
Safflower?

105
00:06:25,618 --> 00:06:29,648
Thanks to you, I finally have family in the countryside.

106
00:06:29,792 --> 00:06:33,230
So, I'm making the most of it!

107
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:36,331
Give me a break!

108
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:44,272
Rather than stay in that old house, why not treat yourself to a fancy hotel for once?

109
00:06:44,383 --> 00:06:46,478
Maybe you'd meet a nice boy.

110
00:06:46,731 --> 00:06:48,959
No way.

111
00:06:48,979 --> 00:06:51,207
You mean a hotel like "Onoya"?

112
00:06:51,329 --> 00:06:52,729
"Onoya"?

113
00:06:54,901 --> 00:06:56,962
Not that again!

114
00:06:57,773 --> 00:07:00,242
You've got to get over it.

115
00:07:00,344 --> 00:07:03,407
Let go of that baggage from the past!

116
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:17,798
My sisters, of course, would never go to a place like atami.

117
00:07:19,477 --> 00:07:21,777
Grandma...

118
00:07:22,882 --> 00:07:24,681
Almost done?

119
00:07:25,620 --> 00:07:27,453
Let's go to another bath.

120
00:07:27,558 --> 00:07:29,959
We just went.

121
00:07:30,061 --> 00:07:32,691
Only to the Swan Bath.

122
00:07:34,836 --> 00:07:46,085
Bored to tears, I went alone to the Brothers Grimm Bath the Mermaid Bath, the Lemon Bath, and the Violet Bath, one after the other.

123
00:07:46,189 --> 00:07:48,215
It's enormous!

124
00:07:48,794 --> 00:07:52,254
When I got to the Roman Bath, my head was spinning.

125
00:07:53,868 --> 00:07:55,963
It's amazing...

126
00:08:05,990 --> 00:08:07,686
And I fainted.

127
00:08:08,561 --> 00:08:11,259
And with that, my trip was over.

128
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:15,134
Followed by endless weeks of vacation.

129
00:08:29,262 --> 00:08:34,863
The other day, my sisters and I were reminiscing.

130
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:43,213
We couldn't stop laughing as the memories came flooding back.

131
00:08:48,162 --> 00:08:49,323
Had one before?

132
00:08:49,431 --> 00:08:51,127
No, it's my first time.

133
00:08:51,567 --> 00:08:53,263
I'm the one who asked for it.

134
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:54,599
Yeah, we know.

135
00:08:54,706 --> 00:08:56,972
Where did you buy it?

136
00:08:57,077 --> 00:08:58,443
Senbikiya in Ginza.

137
00:08:58,546 --> 00:09:00,014
Must have been expensive.

138
00:09:01,517 --> 00:09:03,213
How do we eat it?

139
00:09:03,321 --> 00:09:04,549
Slice it into rings.

140
00:09:04,656 --> 00:09:06,125
But how?

141
00:09:08,129 --> 00:09:09,563
I don't know.

142
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,965
Didn't you ask in the store?

143
00:09:18,948 --> 00:09:20,974
We'll eat it next Sunday.

144
00:09:21,084 --> 00:09:23,486
Why not now?!

145
00:09:24,156 --> 00:09:26,149
We don't know how.

146
00:09:28,965 --> 00:09:30,831
I'll have a banana.

147
00:09:30,934 --> 00:09:32,562
Me too.

148
00:09:36,043 --> 00:09:40,380
Strange fruit they have in those hot countries.

149
00:09:43,256 --> 00:09:44,690
I'm home!

150
00:09:45,058 --> 00:09:47,028
I know how to eat the pineapple!

151
00:09:47,129 --> 00:09:48,427
Really?

152
00:09:53,206 --> 00:09:54,606
I'll take that.

153
00:09:55,342 --> 00:09:56,640
Mind your fingers.

154
00:09:56,745 --> 00:09:59,045
Wouldn't a carving knife be best?

155
00:10:12,238 --> 00:10:14,231
What a nice smell.

156
00:10:23,524 --> 00:10:25,551
It smells so good.

157
00:10:28,032 --> 00:10:29,432
I see.

158
00:10:30,512 --> 00:10:31,238
Get plates.

159
00:10:31,258 --> 00:10:31,984
Quick.

160
00:10:32,105 --> 00:10:34,371
Okay.

161
00:10:36,179 --> 00:10:37,442
Let us eat.

162
00:10:59,185 --> 00:11:00,949
It's hard.

163
00:11:05,262 --> 00:11:06,992
It's not very good.

164
00:11:07,098 --> 00:11:08,657
Not so sweet.

165
00:11:08,768 --> 00:11:10,829
Nothing like the canned stuff.

166
00:11:10,939 --> 00:11:14,776
Live long enough and you see lots of different things.

167
00:11:20,098 --> 00:11:21,245
- You can have mine.

168
00:11:21,265 --> 00:11:22,412
- Mine too.

169
00:11:52,109 --> 00:11:53,873
It's delicious...

170
00:11:59,354 --> 00:12:01,654
Don't force yourself.

171
00:12:01,759 --> 00:12:03,352
You'll get a stomachache.

172
00:12:12,209 --> 00:12:15,579
What a let down.

173
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:20,451
Bananas taste much better.

174
00:12:20,557 --> 00:12:21,786
You're so right.

175
00:12:21,893 --> 00:12:25,024
Bananas are still the king of fruits.

176
00:12:25,132 --> 00:12:26,395
I ll have one now.

177
00:12:51,110 --> 00:12:56,848
The king of fruit is...

178
00:12:57,386 --> 00:12:59,219
the banana, after all.

179
00:13:04,466 --> 00:13:09,202
The year I fainted at the baths and had my first pineapple...

180
00:13:09,674 --> 00:13:16,984
the Beatles came to Japan, started the rock 'n'roll band and electric guitar craze.

181
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:25,296
My sister Nanako, a freshman in art school, was up on all the trends.

182
00:13:26,069 --> 00:13:28,471
Yeah, the Beatles'lyrics are great.

183
00:13:28,574 --> 00:13:36,281
When she wore a mini-skirt, she'd cover her bottom going up the stairs.

184
00:13:39,125 --> 00:13:44,692
My clever sister, Yaeko, was crazy about some Takarazuka actress.

185
00:13:44,801 --> 00:13:46,133
Yaeko...

186
00:13:47,472 --> 00:13:49,168
I told you to knock!

187
00:13:53,482 --> 00:13:58,856
My sisters' memories are mainly of fashion and pop trends.

188
00:13:59,259 --> 00:14:04,223
For them, 1966 is the height of nostalgia.

189
00:14:04,568 --> 00:14:08,166
Whereas I was only ten years old.

190
00:14:09,176 --> 00:14:12,945
My favorite band had yet to debut....

191
00:14:13,049 --> 00:14:17,682
My only memories are the back and forth between school and home.

192
00:14:17,790 --> 00:14:19,760
...mine was pinned on the wall!

193
00:14:19,861 --> 00:14:22,023
That's nice.

194
00:14:22,599 --> 00:14:26,504
And it might be entered in an essay contest.

195
00:14:26,606 --> 00:14:29,202
So, teacher kept it.

196
00:14:29,688 --> 00:14:31,370
- I'd be so happy...

197
00:14:31,390 --> 00:14:33,072
- You didn't finish lunch again.

198
00:14:33,952 --> 00:14:36,252
Why do you hide the pickles inside the bread?

199
00:14:36,356 --> 00:14:38,257
'Cause I hate them.

200
00:14:38,369 --> 00:14:40,148
I've got to throw it away.

201
00:14:40,168 --> 00:14:41,947
What a waste.

202
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:44,533
Such a picky eater!

203
00:14:45,371 --> 00:14:51,541
I'd rather you were a good eater than a good essay writer.

204
00:15:07,910 --> 00:15:11,279
How can you drink that stuff?

205
00:15:12,862 --> 00:15:14,794
Milk's okay.

206
00:15:14,814 --> 00:15:16,746
It's onions I hate.

207
00:15:16,858 --> 00:15:20,524
I'm leaving carrots so I've got no choice.

208
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:25,965
Who decided we can only leave one thing?

209
00:15:26,074 --> 00:15:27,201
Shall I drink it?

210
00:15:27,310 --> 00:15:28,539
Would you?

211
00:15:28,879 --> 00:15:31,873
You'll eat my onions next time?

212
00:15:44,349 --> 00:15:45,478
- Carrots?

213
00:15:45,498 --> 00:15:46,627
- We're allowed one thing!

214
00:15:56,025 --> 00:15:57,891
Two bowls is gross.

215
00:15:58,830 --> 00:16:01,323
People who run in the corridor...

216
00:16:01,435 --> 00:16:06,536
...when the hall monitor says stop, should be punished.

217
00:16:07,011 --> 00:16:10,073
How are you gonna do that?

218
00:16:10,183 --> 00:16:12,050
They shouldn't do it.

219
00:16:12,287 --> 00:16:13,345
That's right.

220
00:16:13,522 --> 00:16:15,423
You might bump into someone.

221
00:16:15,525 --> 00:16:19,862
If I bumped into you I'd bounce a mile!

222
00:16:19,966 --> 00:16:21,093
Get lost!

223
00:16:22,971 --> 00:16:25,669
Running is no big deal.

224
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:26,869
I agree!

225
00:16:27,088 --> 00:16:28,770
- Let's change the rule.

226
00:16:28,790 --> 00:16:30,472
- But we already decided.

227
00:16:31,219 --> 00:16:33,212
Raise your hand if you want to speak.

228
00:16:33,766 --> 00:16:34,759
- Here!

229
00:16:34,779 --> 00:16:35,772
- Miss Tani.

230
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:43,963
The hall monitor should chase the offender, catch them and punish them.

231
00:16:45,453 --> 00:16:46,133
Mr.

232
00:16:46,153 --> 00:16:46,833
Suzuki.

233
00:16:48,014 --> 00:16:51,748
Then the hall monitor should be punished for running too.

234
00:16:51,864 --> 00:16:52,561
He's right!

235
00:16:52,581 --> 00:16:53,278
He's right!

236
00:16:53,757 --> 00:16:55,248
Way to go!

237
00:16:55,460 --> 00:16:56,428
He's right.

238
00:16:57,029 --> 00:16:58,520
Miss Tani.

239
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:03,900
The hall monitor shouldn't be punished because...

240
00:17:04,876 --> 00:17:09,543
...it's like a policeman chasing a speeding car.

241
00:17:15,862 --> 00:17:18,024
Any objections?

242
00:17:20,036 --> 00:17:21,664
It makes sense...

243
00:17:21,772 --> 00:17:23,502
No more running.

244
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:29,416
So, the hall monitor can chase offenders.

245
00:17:31,555 --> 00:17:33,023
Any other issues?

246
00:17:34,260 --> 00:17:35,660
Miss Tani.

247
00:17:36,340 --> 00:17:37,082
- Her again.

248
00:17:37,102 --> 00:17:37,844
- Busybody.

249
00:17:37,966 --> 00:17:39,298
Be quiet.

250
00:17:39,401 --> 00:17:41,803
Some people don't finish lunch.

251
00:17:42,341 --> 00:17:47,008
I just read an article on the Vietnam War.

252
00:17:47,349 --> 00:17:50,981
There are many unfortunate people overseas.

253
00:17:51,089 --> 00:17:52,648
We're very lucky.

254
00:17:52,758 --> 00:17:54,659
Lucky to have you near me!

255
00:17:57,867 --> 00:18:01,305
We should be grateful for our food.

256
00:18:01,406 --> 00:18:08,149
We're allowed to leave one thing on our plates, but I think it's wrong!

257
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:13,522
Goody two-shoes.

258
00:18:13,971 --> 00:18:16,183
- It can't hurt to leave one thing.

259
00:18:16,203 --> 00:18:18,415
- Let's all leave milk...

260
00:18:18,545 --> 00:18:20,108
- Give it to someone else...

261
00:18:20,128 --> 00:18:21,691
- Of course.

262
00:18:21,818 --> 00:18:23,847
- People hide leftovers in bread.

263
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:25,896
- That's cheating!

264
00:18:26,115 --> 00:18:28,050
I hate school food.

265
00:18:28,419 --> 00:18:30,855
If you want to speak, raise your hand!

266
00:18:31,624 --> 00:18:34,117
What a revolting situation.

267
00:18:37,067 --> 00:18:49,309
That night in bed, after chatting to my sisters more memories from fifth grade came rushing back.

268
00:18:52,369 --> 00:18:54,682
Our pet dog... .

269
00:18:54,702 --> 00:18:57,015
School sports day...

270
00:18:57,869 --> 00:19:00,465
being scared by gross horror comics....

271
00:19:01,843 --> 00:19:04,507
longing for an electric pencil-sharpener...

272
00:19:06,283 --> 00:19:10,347
So many little details, one after the other...

273
00:19:10,824 --> 00:19:17,925
playing in my head like a movie, almost overpowering me.

274
00:19:23,179 --> 00:19:24,704
Is there a Miss Okajima here?

275
00:19:26,384 --> 00:19:27,374
That's her.

276
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:42,673
Hirota in our class says he likes you.

